{
  "id": 104,
  "languageId": 2,
  "title": "Commands",
  "objective": "Learn how to issue imperative orders to a single person.",
  "content": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "data": {
        "text": "Klingons do not make polite requests. They give orders. To command a single person to do something, you usually add the prefix 'yI-' to the start of a verb."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "word",
      "data": {
        "ref": "yIqIm",
        "description": "Pay attention! (Often yelled by a commanding officer before speaking)."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "word",
      "data": {
        "ref": "yIghoS",
        "description": "Approach! / Come here! / Proceed! (Used to order someone to move toward you or a target)."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "word",
      "data": {
        "ref": "yIHIv",
        "description": "Attack! (From the verb 'HIv', meaning to attack)."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "type": "word",
      "data": {
        "ref": "yIba'",
        "description": "Sit! (A blunt command to take a seat)."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "type": "exercise",
      "data": {
        "exerciseType": "multiple_choice",
        "question": "What prefix do you add to a verb to make it a command to a single person?",
        "options": [
          { "text": "nuq-", "correct": false },
          { "text": "yI-", "correct": true },
          { "text": "batlh-", "correct": false },
          { "text": "pe-", "correct": false }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "type": "exercise",
      "data": {
        "exerciseType": "fill_in_blank",
        "instruction": "Complete the dialogue.",
        "sentence": "Commander: \"Enemy ship sighted! _____!\"",
        "answer": "yIHIv",
        "hint": "The order to attack.",
        "options": ["yIba'", "yIHIv", "yIqIm", "yIghoS"]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "type": "exercise",
      "data": {
        "exerciseType": "fill_in_blank",
        "instruction": "Complete the dialogue.",
        "sentence": "Officer: \"_____! The General is speaking!\"",
        "answer": "yIqIm",
        "hint": "The order to pay attention.",
        "options": ["yIba'", "yIHIv", "yIqIm", "yIghoS"]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "type": "text",
      "data": {
        "text": "Excellent. You now know how to bark orders like a true Klingon officer. pItlh! (Done!)"
      }
    }
  ]
}